                <div class="tab-pane fade" id="v-pills-mammals" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="v-pills-mammals-tab">
                    <h2>Mammals</h2>
                    <p>Both grey and red foxes call the Park their home, and kits (youngsters) of both species are observed at the Park every year.</p>
                    <p>The foxes are often seen at dawn and dusk, hunting, playing or just walking down the trails.</p>
                    <p>Other mammals that live in the Park include mink, woodchucks, muskrats, various mice and voles, and an occasional rabbit, coyote or deer.</p>
